 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2016/changing-order-of-tray-and-i3status-on-i3bar/?answer=2041#post-id-2041</link><description>There is no such functionality in i3 (i3bar). Checking the source, the location of the tray icons is hard-coded to the right (which makes sense, actually). So, I guess your alternative would be to suggest it as a feature to the mailing list, before patching any code yourself.

Reference: [http://code.stapelberg.de/git/i3/tree/i3bar/src/xcb.c?h=next](http://code.stapelberg.de/git/i3/tree/i3bar/src/xcb.c?h=next)

and check function configure_trayclients().</description><pubDate>Mon, 17 Jun 2013 04:07:55 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2016/changing-order-of-tray-and-i3status-on-i3bar/?answer=2041#post-id-2041</guid></item><item><title>Comment by Michael for &lt;p&gt;There is no such functionality in i3 (i3bar). Checking the source, the location of the tray icons is hard-coded to the right (which makes sense, actually). So, I guess your alternative would be to suggest it as a feature to the mailing list, before patching any code yourself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reference: &lt;a href="http://code.stapelberg.de/git/i3/tree/i3bar/src/xcb.c?h=next"&gt;http://code.stapelberg.de/git/i3/tree/i3bar/src/xcb.c?h=next&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and check function configure_trayclients().&lt;/p&gt;
